Stovetop Mac and Cheese
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 1/2 c water
1 c whole milk
8 oz macaroni
1 c deli american cheese, grated
1 c extra sharp cheddar, grated
dash cayenne
1/2 dijon mustard
salt and pepper to taste

Bring water and milk to a boil in medium saucepan. Add macaroni, bring to a simmer, lower heat, and cook 6-8 min, pasta should be just past al-dente. Add cayenne, mustard, american cheese and stir in, ~1 min. Take off heat, add cheddar and stir in. Cover with lid and let sit until all cheese is melted.

1/3 c panko
1 tbsp olive oil
salt and pepper to taste
2 tbsp parmesan

Toast in a skillet on stove top, stirring constantly, until golden brown. Add parmesan after taking off stage.

Serve mac and cheese, top with breadcrumb mixture.
